This paper is about developing a neural discourse segmenter, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a BiLSTM-CRF framework, which is a common approach in deep learning, suggesting that it could also be categorized as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of data insufficiency, which is a common issue in machine learning, indicating that it could also be categorized as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on the RST-DT corpus, which is a dataset commonly used in information retrieval research, suggesting that it could also be categorized as cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
